    "body" : "<h2>tl;dr</h2>\n<pre><code>String cleanString = dirtyString.strip() ; // Call new `String::strip` method.\n</code></pre>\n<h2><code>String::strip…</code></h2>\n<p>The old <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#trim()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>String::trim</code></a> method has a <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20200929003217/https://closingbraces.net/2008/11/11/javastringtrim/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">strange definition</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whitespace_character\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">whitespace</a>.</p>\n<p>As discussed <a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/applying-new-jdk-11-string-methods\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">here</a>, Java 11 adds new <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#strip()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>strip…</code></a> methods to the <code>String</code> class. These use a more Unicode-savvy definition of whitespace. See the rules of this definition in the class JavaDoc for <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Character.html#isWhitespace(int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Character::isWhitespace</code></a>.</p>\n<p>Example code.</p>\n<pre><code>String input = &quot; some Thing &quot;;\nSystem.out.println(&quot;before-&gt;&gt;&quot;+input+&quot;&lt;&lt;-&quot;);\ninput = input.strip();\nSystem.out.println(&quot;after-&gt;&gt;&quot;+input+&quot;&lt;&lt;-&quot;);\n</code></pre>\n<p>Or you can strip <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#stripLeading()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">just the leading</a> or <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#stripTrailing()\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">just the trailing</a> whitespace.</p>\n<h3>Codepoints defining <em>whitespace</em></h3>\n<p>You do not mention exactly what <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Code_point\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">code point(s)</a> make up your newlines. I imagine your newline is likely included in the following lists of code points targeted by <code>strip</code>, those defined by <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/23/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Character.html#isWhitespace(int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Character.isWhitespace</code></a>.</p>\n<h4><code>Character.SPACE_SEPARATOR</code></h4>\n<div class=\"s-table-container\"><table class=\"s-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: right;\">Decimal</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Hex</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Name</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">32</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+0020</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">5,760</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+1680</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">OGHAM SPACE MARK</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,192</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2000</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">EN QUAD</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,193</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2001</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">EM QUAD</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,194</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2002</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">EN SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,195</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2003</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">EM SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,196</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2004</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">THREE-PER-EM SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,197</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2005</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">FOUR-PER-EM SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,198</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2006</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">SIX-PER-EM SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,200</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2008</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">PUNCTUATION SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,201</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2009</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">THIN SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,202</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+200A</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">HAIR SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,287</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+205F</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">MEDIUM MATHEMATICAL SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">12,288</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+3000</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">IDEOGRAPHIC SPACE</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<h4><code>Character.LINE_SEPARATOR</code></h4>\n<div class=\"s-table-container\"><table class=\"s-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: right;\">Decimal</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Hex</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Name</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,232</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2028</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">LINE SEPARATOR</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<h4><code>Character.PARAGRAPH_SEPARATOR</code></h4>\n<div class=\"s-table-container\"><table class=\"s-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: right;\">Decimal</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Hex</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Name</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">8,233</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">U+2029</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">PARAGRAPH SEPARATOR</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<h4>Other</h4>\n<div class=\"s-table-container\"><table class=\"s-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Literal</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: right;\">Hex</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Decimal</th>\n<th>Name</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\t'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+0009</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">9</td>\n<td>HORIZONTAL TABULATION</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\n'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+000A</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">10</td>\n<td>LINE FEED</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\u000B'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+000B</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">11</td>\n<td>VERTICAL TABULATION</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\f'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+000C</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">12</td>\n<td>FORM FEED</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\r'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+000D</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">13</td>\n<td>CARRIAGE RETURN</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\u001C'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+001C</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">28</td>\n<td>FILE SEPARATOR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\u001D'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+001D</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">29</td>\n<td>GROUP SEPARATOR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\u001E'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+001E</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">30</td>\n<td>RECORD SEPARATOR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\u001F'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+001F</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">31</td>\n<td>UNIT SEPARATOR</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<p>\uD83D\uDC49\uD83C\uDFFD  The key to solving your problem is two items in that last table. Most commonly, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newline\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">newlines</a> are either LINE FEED or CARRIAGE RETURN, or a combination of the two.</p>\n<div class=\"s-table-container\"><table class=\"s-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: center;\">Literal</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: right;\">Hex</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Decimal</th>\n<th>Name</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\n'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+000A</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">10</td>\n<td>LINE FEED</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">'\\r'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: right;\">U+000D</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\">13</td>\n<td>CARRIAGE RETURN</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<hr />\n<p>By the way, you may be curious to see the code I wrote to determine which characters matched the criteria of the first bullet of requirements specified in the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/23/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Character.html#isWhitespace(int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Character.isWhitespace</code></a> Javadoc:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>• It is a Unicode space character (<code>SPACE_SEPARATOR</code>, <code>LINE_SEPARATOR</code>, or <code>PARAGRAPH_SEPARATOR</code>) but is not also a non-breaking space ('\\u00A0', '\\u2007', '\\u202F').</p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>public class Whitespace\n{\n    public static void main ( String[] args )\n    {\n        final Collection &lt; Integer &gt; nonBreakingSpaceCodePoints = List.of (\n                0x00A0 ,  // NO-BREAK SPACE = decimal 160.\n                0x2007 ,  // FIGURE SPACE = decimal 8,199.\n                0x202F    // NARROW NO-BREAK SPACE = decimal 8,239.\n        );\n        final Locale locale = Locale.of ( &quot;en&quot; , &quot;US&quot; ); // Determines the decimal grouping separator in `printf` below.\n\n        for\n        ( byte category :\n                List.of (\n                        Character.SPACE_SEPARATOR ,    // General category &quot;Zs&quot; in the Unicode specification. `byte` value = 12.\n                        Character.LINE_SEPARATOR ,     // General category &quot;Zl&quot; in the Unicode specification. `byte` value = 13.\n                        Character.PARAGRAPH_SEPARATOR  // General category &quot;Zp&quot; in the Unicode specification. `byte` value = 14.\n                )\n        )\n        {\n            System.out.println ( &quot;------------|  category = &quot; + category + &quot;  |-------------------------------------------------&quot; );\n            for ( int codePoint = Character.MIN_CODE_POINT ; codePoint &lt;= Character.MAX_CODE_POINT ; codePoint++ )  // Loop through every one of the 1,114,112 code points.\n            {\n                if (      // If this character is considered to be whitespace according to the `Character.isWhitespace` method, according to the first bullet of the criteria listed in the Javadoc.\n                        Character.isDefined ( codePoint ) // A valid Unicode code point number, assigned a character in Unicode.\n                                &amp;&amp; Character.getType ( codePoint ) == category  // The Unicode category of the character assigned to this code point.\n                                &amp;&amp; ( ! nonBreakingSpaceCodePoints.contains ( codePoint ) )  // This character is *not* a non-breaking space character.\n                )\n                {\n                    System.out.printf ( locale , &quot;%, 7d = U+%04X: %s%n&quot; , codePoint , codePoint , Character.getName ( codePoint ) );   // Print the code point and its corresponding character representation\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Results:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>------------|  category = 12  |-------------------------------------------------\n     32 = U+0020: SPACE\n  5,760 = U+1680: OGHAM SPACE MARK\n  8,192 = U+2000: EN QUAD\n  8,193 = U+2001: EM QUAD\n  8,194 = U+2002: EN SPACE\n  8,195 = U+2003: EM SPACE\n  8,196 = U+2004: THREE-PER-EM SPACE\n  8,197 = U+2005: FOUR-PER-EM SPACE\n  8,198 = U+2006: SIX-PER-EM SPACE\n  8,200 = U+2008: PUNCTUATION SPACE\n  8,201 = U+2009: THIN SPACE\n  8,202 = U+200A: HAIR SPACE\n  8,287 = U+205F: MEDIUM MATHEMATICAL SPACE\n 12,288 = U+3000: IDEOGRAPHIC SPACE\n------------|  category = 13  |-------------------------------------------------\n  8,232 = U+2028: LINE SEPARATOR\n------------|  category = 14  |-------------------------------------------------\n  8,233 = U+2029: PARAGRAPH SEPARATOR\n</code></pre>\n"
